WEBVTT

00:03.699 --> 00:04.047
.

00:04.091 --> 00:07.094
- Crime stats are much higher
than we would like,

00:07.137 --> 00:09.661
but we are very proud
of the progress we've made

00:09.705 --> 00:10.836
in the past ten months.

00:10.880 --> 00:13.404
Newly hired officers
now reflect the faces

00:13.448 --> 00:14.971
of the districts they patrol.

00:15.015 --> 00:17.582
Community policing is in place,

00:17.626 --> 00:20.846
and the neighborhoods are
responding in a positive way.

00:20.890 --> 00:24.198
Look, we know change
isn't easy,

00:24.241 --> 00:26.983
but we are dedicated
to transparency

00:27.027 --> 00:29.855
and rule of law,
and we will persevere.

00:29.899 --> 00:31.292
Thank you.

00:31.335 --> 00:33.642
- Deputy Miller, Deputy Miller!
Deputy Miller.

00:33.685 --> 00:36.558
Five officers have recently
been suspended or fired

00:36.601 --> 00:39.343
due to police misconduct.
How is that progress?

00:39.387 --> 00:41.650
- [scoffs]
You just said it.

00:41.693 --> 00:44.479
They've been suspended
or fired.

00:44.522 --> 00:46.350
It means
we're paying attention,

00:46.394 --> 00:48.526
and we're holding people
accountable.

00:48.570 --> 00:51.529
They are part of a culture that
will no longer be tolerated.

00:51.573 --> 00:52.704
[chatter]

00:52.748 --> 00:54.924
- As a result
of this misconduct,

00:54.967 --> 00:58.536
several violent offenders have
recently been exonerated.

00:58.580 --> 01:01.800
I'm talking
about murderers, rapists.

01:01.844 --> 01:04.368
What do you say to the victims
and their families?

01:04.412 --> 01:07.284
- I say justice will prevail
in the end...

01:07.328 --> 01:08.851
[dramatic music]

01:08.894 --> 01:11.636
And that we must solve crimes
the right way.

01:11.680 --> 01:13.812
The legal way.

01:13.856 --> 01:17.729
Change isn't always easy
or pretty,

01:17.773 --> 01:20.080
but that doesn't mean
it's not necessary.

01:20.123 --> 01:21.646
♪

01:21.690 --> 01:23.692
- Units in the 13th District,

01:23.735 --> 01:25.302
we're getting calls
of a man shot.

01:25.346 --> 01:26.912
4100 block of South Wallace.

01:26.956 --> 01:28.697
CFD has been notified
and is en route.

01:30.133 --> 01:33.571
- 5021, hold me down responding
to the Wallace call.

01:33.615 --> 01:36.922
I'm three blocks out.
- Copy that.

01:36.966 --> 01:39.925
[dramatic music]

01:39.969 --> 01:46.802
♪

01:46.845 --> 01:48.282
- Hey, step back.

01:48.325 --> 01:50.022
Why don't you guys
wait over there?

01:50.066 --> 01:52.460
I'm Sergeant Voight,
and I can help you.

01:52.503 --> 01:55.419
Help's on the way.
All right.

01:55.463 --> 01:56.942
I'm gonna put pressure
on the wound.

01:56.986 --> 01:58.944
- [groaning]

01:58.988 --> 02:00.250
- Can you tell me
what happened?

02:00.294 --> 02:01.991
- Oh, he shot me.
The bastard shot me.

02:02.034 --> 02:03.123
- Okay, who shot you?

02:03.166 --> 02:04.602
- Quick Route driver.
- All right.

02:04.646 --> 02:07.257
- Picked us up,
then started driving.

02:07.301 --> 02:10.173
- Okay.
- He told me to get out.

02:10.217 --> 02:13.394
He's got my wife.
You gotta help her.

02:13.437 --> 02:15.135
He's driving
a black Ford Fusion.

02:15.178 --> 02:16.962
- Where'd you get picked up?

02:17.006 --> 02:18.486
- 31st.
- 31st.

02:18.529 --> 02:20.096
- 31st...
[siren wailing]

02:20.140 --> 02:22.098
- Hey, hey, stay with me.

02:22.142 --> 02:23.404
What's your name?

02:23.447 --> 02:24.796
- Ben.
- Ben, all right.

02:24.840 --> 02:26.711
Hang in there, Ben.
The ambulance is here.

02:26.755 --> 02:28.844
Can you tell me
what the driver looked like?

02:28.887 --> 02:30.715
- Black Ford Fusion.

02:30.759 --> 02:33.196
- Okay.
Let me see.

02:33.240 --> 02:35.764
It'll be okay.

02:35.807 --> 02:37.896
- 5021, emergency.

02:37.940 --> 02:39.463
Suspect in recent shooting

02:39.507 --> 02:42.597
is fleeing westbound
in a black Ford Fusion.

02:42.640 --> 02:46.383
Advise responding units
to exercise extreme caution.

02:46.427 --> 02:49.299
Gunshot victim's wife
is in the vehicle,

02:49.343 --> 02:50.822
appears to have been abducted.

02:50.866 --> 02:52.607
- Copy that.

02:56.611 --> 03:00.354
So the woman abducted
is his wife, Jessica Larson.

03:00.397 --> 03:02.878
I want an ASA onboard now.
This could move fast.

03:02.921 --> 03:04.836
- I'm on it, Sarge.
- We're pulling video.

03:04.880 --> 03:06.534
Hopefully, we'll get enough
for facial rec.

03:06.577 --> 03:08.144
- Got it.
All right.

03:08.188 --> 03:09.537
So where we at on phones?

03:09.580 --> 03:11.234
- Ben's is locked,
the wife's is off,

03:11.278 --> 03:12.279
but we're working
with Quick Route

03:12.322 --> 03:13.323
to help us locate the vehicle.

03:13.367 --> 03:14.629
- I got a list
of all the pickups

03:14.672 --> 03:16.326
in the last 30 minutes
in the immediate area.

03:16.370 --> 03:18.372
- Just focus
on a black Ford Fusion,

03:18.415 --> 03:21.549
about 7:15 on
or about 31st and Dearborn.

03:21.592 --> 03:23.115
- Fusion, copy that.
Running that account.

03:23.159 --> 03:24.508
- All right,
run that plate by me.

03:24.552 --> 03:26.989
- Paul Victor
Boy 27 David William.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.338
- Stand by.
Stand by.

03:28.382 --> 03:29.774
We're looking
for a Jonathan Eakin.

03:29.818 --> 03:32.821
DOB 14 January 1989.

03:32.864 --> 03:36.303
- All right, yeah, I got him.
I got him.

03:36.346 --> 03:38.783
Jonathan Eakin.
One prior for drug possession.

03:38.827 --> 03:41.612
- Yeah.
- Let's find this guy.

03:44.354 --> 03:46.530
- Any updates?

03:46.574 --> 03:48.967
- Quick Route's tech's still
saying he's on this block.

03:50.708 --> 03:51.927
There he is.

03:51.970 --> 03:53.407
- Sarge, we got a positive
on the vehicle.

03:53.450 --> 03:54.930
He's heading south on Dempsey.
Ruz, you copy?

03:54.973 --> 03:56.714
- Copy that.
We're coming around.

03:56.758 --> 03:58.455
- Copy.
On my way.

03:58.499 --> 04:01.502
[dramatic music]

04:01.545 --> 04:04.287
♪

04:04.331 --> 04:07.725
[tires screeching]

04:09.292 --> 04:11.076
- Chicago PD!
Let me see your hands.

04:11.120 --> 04:12.252
Nice and slow.

04:12.295 --> 04:14.297
Reach for the door
and step out of the car.

04:14.341 --> 04:15.777
Step out of the vehicle.

04:15.820 --> 04:17.474
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

04:17.518 --> 04:19.171
- Step back.
On your knees, on your knees!

04:19.215 --> 04:21.086
- What did I do?

04:21.130 --> 04:22.436
- Car's clear!

04:22.479 --> 04:24.307
- Trunk's empty!

04:24.351 --> 04:27.528
- We wanna know
about your pickup, 7:15.

04:27.571 --> 04:30.835
- Jessica Larson.
Where is she?

04:30.879 --> 04:33.316
- Larson?
Who?

04:33.360 --> 04:34.578
Wait, wait.Larson?

04:34.622 --> 04:36.232
She was a no-show.
I one-starred her ass.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.582
Check my phone.
- Let me see.

04:38.626 --> 04:40.149
- It's right there, see?
"Customers not at pickup."

04:40.192 --> 04:41.977
I've never seen her before
in my life, I swear to God.

04:44.501 --> 04:46.373
- Bring him in.
- I didn't do anything.

04:46.416 --> 04:47.983
- Then you got nothing
to worry about.

04:48.026 --> 04:50.507
Keep digging.
She's still out there.

04:54.337 --> 04:55.643
- Morning.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.819
- Sarge, the Quick Route
driver's story checked out.

04:57.862 --> 04:59.560
He was 20 blocks away
when the abduction happened,

04:59.603 --> 05:02.214
so we kicked him.
Any word on the gunshot victim?

05:02.258 --> 05:03.781
- Except him to make
a full recovery.

05:03.825 --> 05:05.914
Med's gonna notify us
as soon as he's stable.

05:05.957 --> 05:08.177
- POD video from 31st
and Dearborn just came in.

05:08.220 --> 05:11.049
That's where Ben and his wife
were picked up.

05:11.093 --> 05:13.095
All right, 7:12,

05:13.138 --> 05:14.662
Larsons exit the restaurant.

05:14.705 --> 05:16.751
Now they're waiting
for their Quick Route.

05:16.794 --> 05:18.274
Hold on.

05:18.318 --> 05:19.623
They're expecting
a black Fusion.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.451
That is a black Honda.
They look almost identical--

05:21.495 --> 05:23.627
- Freeze it.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:23.671 --> 05:24.976
- Run the plate.
- All right.

05:25.020 --> 05:29.329
Illinois plates.
John X-ray 72 Paul nine.

05:29.372 --> 05:30.808
- It's registered
to a Luna Witt.

05:30.852 --> 05:33.376
She's 55,
reported it stolen yesterday.

05:33.420 --> 05:34.551
Here we go.
LEADS posted

05:34.595 --> 05:35.509
that Patrol recovered
the vehicle

05:35.552 --> 05:36.945
in Haywood Park.

05:36.988 --> 05:39.121
- Come on.
Jay, Hailey, you're with me.

05:42.994 --> 05:44.953
- Hey, car was empty.

05:44.996 --> 05:47.477
Surprise, surprise,
the fire was intentional.

05:47.521 --> 05:49.087
They doused the inside
with lighter fluid.

05:49.131 --> 05:51.176
- Right, thanks, Bos.

05:51.220 --> 05:52.569
All right, notify the others.
[cell phone buzzes]

05:52.613 --> 05:53.918
We're gonna conduct
a grid search.

05:53.962 --> 05:56.268
PODs, cameras, do the drill.
- Upton.

05:56.312 --> 05:57.835
Sarge, it's CPIC.
Hold on a sec.

05:57.879 --> 06:00.490
I'm gonna put you on speaker.
Go ahead.

06:00.534 --> 06:02.013
- The provider
just sent over the dump

06:02.057 --> 06:04.102
on Jess Larson's phone.
You guys should be looking

06:04.146 --> 06:06.496
at the 2500 block
of West Howard.

06:06.540 --> 06:07.758
- That's close.
Let's go.

06:07.802 --> 06:10.195
- All right.
We're headed there now, thanks.

06:10.239 --> 06:13.024
[dramatic music]

06:13.068 --> 06:18.116
♪

06:18.160 --> 06:20.292
- This is the only building
in the 2500 block.

06:20.336 --> 06:22.425
- We got a way in.
- Let's go.

06:22.469 --> 06:29.606
♪

07:20.309 --> 07:22.050
- Sarge.

07:32.626 --> 07:36.194
Jay, we got her.
It's a recovery, not a rescue.

07:36.238 --> 07:39.197
[somber music]

07:39.241 --> 07:43.245
♪

07:43.288 --> 07:45.595
- Excellent.

07:45.639 --> 07:47.118
Sarge.
- Anything?

07:47.162 --> 07:49.338
- So far, nothing actionable
from the body.

07:49.381 --> 07:50.513
The rape kit's being rushed.

07:50.557 --> 07:51.688
There's no fingerprints
on the scene.

07:51.732 --> 07:53.081
They think he used a condom.

07:53.124 --> 07:54.604
Cause of death
is strangulation.

07:54.648 --> 07:56.171
- But she fought back.

07:56.214 --> 07:57.564
There's plenty
of defensive wounds.

07:57.607 --> 07:59.087
Her fingernails
are ripped off, broken.

07:59.130 --> 08:00.610
They're conducting
the scrapings now.

08:00.654 --> 08:02.264
Hopefully, we'll get DNA.

08:02.307 --> 08:03.657
- Okay, so what do we know
about this place?

08:03.700 --> 08:05.702
- All right, well, the company
that owns the building

08:05.746 --> 08:07.356
says it's used
for heavy equipment storage,

08:07.399 --> 08:08.879
and it's empty
most of the time.

08:08.923 --> 08:10.794
We got tire tracks
that are consistent

08:10.838 --> 08:12.361
with the size
of our burnt down Honda.

08:12.404 --> 08:13.623
Found pretty good blind spot,

08:13.667 --> 08:15.059
parked away
from all the damn cameras.

08:15.103 --> 08:17.235
- It worked.
I got into the security area.

08:17.279 --> 08:19.542
I got nothing on surveillance
inside or out.

08:19.586 --> 08:21.196
- So this prick
knows this place.

08:21.239 --> 08:22.632
- Yeah, he most certainly does.

08:22.676 --> 08:25.505
He worked there for six months
in 2015.

08:25.548 --> 08:26.984
- What are you talking about?

08:27.028 --> 08:28.812
- I pulled CTA footage from
where the Honda was stolen.

08:28.856 --> 08:30.466
There's no footage
of the steal,

08:30.510 --> 08:33.382
but I noticed a guy walking out
of a minimart a block away.

08:33.425 --> 08:36.080
That right there is Caleb Hoff.

08:36.124 --> 08:37.821
- He looks familiar.
- He should.

08:37.865 --> 08:39.997
He just sued the city
for 25 mil.

08:40.041 --> 08:41.869
- Yeah, I know this guy.
Wrongful arrest.

08:41.912 --> 08:44.828
- He was serving 20 to life
for rape and murder.

08:44.872 --> 08:47.570
The Conviction Integrity Unit
looked into his case.

08:47.614 --> 08:49.180
Next thing you know,
the arresting detective

08:49.224 --> 08:51.835
gets charged
with unlawful use of force,

08:51.879 --> 08:53.271
and Hoff walked free
three weeks ago

08:53.315 --> 08:55.186
with an apology from the mayor.
- Okay.

08:55.230 --> 08:57.841
We're gonna do this one right.
By the book.

08:57.885 --> 09:00.148
Who knows?
Maybe Hoff has bad luck,

09:00.191 --> 09:02.542
lives in the area,
was just buying milk.

09:02.585 --> 09:03.891
- Come on, Sarge.
You really believe that?

09:03.934 --> 09:07.242
- No, but it doesn't change
the game plan.

09:12.943 --> 09:15.598
- That's him.
- And you're sure?

09:15.642 --> 09:17.992
- It was dark out,

09:18.035 --> 09:20.603
but I'll never forget
those eyes,

09:20.647 --> 09:22.779
how he stared,

09:22.823 --> 09:25.477
how he was gawking at Jess
in the rearview mirror.

09:25.521 --> 09:27.305
I knew the guy was trouble.

09:27.349 --> 09:29.569
So I told him to stop the car.

09:29.612 --> 09:32.310
He pulled over.

09:32.354 --> 09:34.225
He told me to get out.

09:34.269 --> 09:35.749
Only me.

09:36.967 --> 09:38.665
I told him to go to hell.

09:39.927 --> 09:42.364
I grabbed Jess's hand
to get out of the car.

09:43.365 --> 09:45.367
That's when he shot me.

09:48.022 --> 09:50.981
You caught him?
He's under arrest?

09:52.853 --> 09:55.159
- Sorry.Not yet.

09:55.203 --> 09:57.205
- Do you know his name?

09:57.858 --> 10:01.078
- It's Caleb Hoff.
- Does he have a record?

10:01.122 --> 10:03.428
- He's done something like this
before, yeah.

10:03.472 --> 10:05.517
- Why isn't he in prison?

10:05.561 --> 10:07.084
What the hell was he doing
on the street?

10:07.128 --> 10:09.086
- Ben, I'm sorry.I am.

10:09.130 --> 10:11.306
It's just the law.It's...

10:13.221 --> 10:14.352
It's the law.

10:14.396 --> 10:16.180
There's nothing
we could do about it.

10:17.268 --> 10:18.835
- To hell with the law!

10:20.663 --> 10:23.623
My wife is dead, Sergeant,

10:23.666 --> 10:26.147
because you let a monster
go free.

10:26.190 --> 10:29.150
[dramatic music]

10:29.193 --> 10:32.588
♪

10:32.632 --> 10:34.068
How could you?

10:42.642 --> 10:42.772
.

10:42.816 --> 10:45.122
- Looks like Caleb Hoff's
in the wind.

10:45.166 --> 10:46.558
He was released
from Stateville five weeks ago,

10:46.602 --> 10:48.691
all charges dropped,
no stipulations to his release.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.911
- So you're telling me he
didn't have to give an address

10:50.954 --> 10:52.129
or report to a PO?

10:52.173 --> 10:53.827
- Correct.
No last known address.

10:53.870 --> 10:55.742
- All right, he got any family
here in Chicago?

10:55.785 --> 10:57.221
- I mean, there's
a couple distant cousins,

10:57.265 --> 10:58.962
and I'm trying
to track them down, but...

10:59.006 --> 11:00.877
- All right,
what about Hoff's attorney?

11:00.921 --> 11:02.400
- Yeah, I reached out to him.

11:02.444 --> 11:03.706
For a defense attorney
hell-bent

11:03.750 --> 11:05.055
on taking apart
the police force,

11:05.099 --> 11:06.753
he was all right.
He leveled with me.

11:06.796 --> 11:08.276
Said he hadn't talked to him
in two weeks,

11:08.319 --> 11:09.756
and that that made him nervous.

11:09.799 --> 11:11.583
- Repeat offending tends
to hurt the money train.

11:11.627 --> 11:13.324
- All right, we get anything
from that minimart?

11:13.368 --> 11:15.413
- Yeah, presented the owner
with a photo array,

11:15.457 --> 11:17.067
and he said he noticed Hoff
right off the bat,

11:17.111 --> 11:18.460
said he was high as hell,

11:18.503 --> 11:20.592
and he bought cigarettes
and a box of condoms.

11:20.636 --> 11:22.638
- Morning.
I don't wanna interrupt.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.553
Hank, you got a sec?
- Yep.

11:24.596 --> 11:25.510
- So it's true?

11:25.554 --> 11:26.773
Caleb Hoff's
a person of interest

11:26.816 --> 11:28.078
in Jess Larson's murder?

11:28.122 --> 11:30.254
- Our victim's husband
gave a positive ID.

11:30.298 --> 11:32.300
We're trying
to locate Hoff now.

11:32.343 --> 11:33.736
- All right, I should put out
a statement.

11:33.780 --> 11:36.652
I need to warn the public
about using ride share apps,

11:36.696 --> 11:39.307
and I should mention
Hoff by name.

11:39.350 --> 11:40.656
- I don't think
we're there yet.

11:40.700 --> 11:41.831
- Why not?

11:41.875 --> 11:44.051
- We got no DNA
or physical evidence.

11:44.094 --> 11:45.443
- You said the victim's husband
ID'd Hoff.

11:45.487 --> 11:47.358
- Yeah, well,
turns out he also had

11:47.402 --> 11:49.273
four scotch and sodas
prior to the incident.

11:49.317 --> 11:50.710
Plus, it was dark outside,

11:50.753 --> 11:53.103
and he only saw his eyes
in the rearview mirror.

11:53.147 --> 11:54.626
I ran it all past the ASA.

11:54.670 --> 11:56.454
He said the ID's
pretty much meaningless.

11:56.498 --> 11:57.717
- All right, all right.

11:57.760 --> 11:59.327
We need more evidence,
we need to make sure

11:59.370 --> 12:01.503
the case is airtight, or this
prick is gonna sue is again.

12:01.546 --> 12:02.939
- Can you believe this?

12:02.983 --> 12:05.507
We're tiptoeing around
a serial rapist and killer,

12:05.550 --> 12:07.639
trying to make sure
we don't offend him.

12:07.683 --> 12:09.903
- You should talk to the
detective who arrested Hoff.

12:09.946 --> 12:12.166
See what she knows.
- The one who got suspended?

12:12.209 --> 12:14.037
- She's a hell of a cop, Hank.

12:14.081 --> 12:16.170
Smart, tough.

12:16.213 --> 12:18.999
She just lost her mind
for a minute.

12:19.042 --> 12:21.653
That's all.
- Hmm.

12:21.697 --> 12:23.655
- And if you do
talk to her directly,

12:23.699 --> 12:26.267
just keep it on the down low,
off the report.

12:26.310 --> 12:29.574
I don't wanna give his lawyers
any more ammunition.

12:30.619 --> 12:31.576
- Copy.

12:40.324 --> 12:42.457
- You're here to talk
about Hoff, correct?

12:42.500 --> 12:44.851
- Well, from what I understand,
you know a lot about him.

12:44.894 --> 12:46.983
You spent a lot of time
on the investigation.

12:47.027 --> 12:50.378
- 18 months, day and night.

12:50.421 --> 12:52.815
So I'm guessing
he already slipped up,

12:52.859 --> 12:54.817
raped and killed someone.

12:54.861 --> 12:58.429
- He's a person of interest
in a current investigation.

12:58.473 --> 13:00.780
- You don't have any leads.

13:00.823 --> 13:03.391
- Not at the moment.

13:03.434 --> 13:05.697
- We were hoping
you could help us out,

13:05.741 --> 13:08.483
shed some light on
his personality, his habits.

13:09.397 --> 13:11.442
- I'll grab my files.

13:11.486 --> 13:14.402
[dramatic music]

13:14.445 --> 13:15.577
♪

13:15.620 --> 13:17.231
Mom died when he was five.

13:17.274 --> 13:20.190
His violent, abusive father
skipped town when he was seven.

13:20.234 --> 13:22.410
Hoff entered
the foster care system.

13:22.453 --> 13:24.368
He did not play well
with others.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.718
- Hoff is violent and abusive,
just like dad.

13:26.762 --> 13:28.633
At 15, he was busted
on two charges,

13:28.677 --> 13:30.722
agg assault and carjacking.

13:30.766 --> 13:33.203
- The driver
was a 16-year-old girl.

13:33.247 --> 13:35.118
Fast forward a few years,

13:35.162 --> 13:37.338
Hoff got picked up for the rape
of a college student

13:37.381 --> 13:39.079
named Nina Capel.

13:39.122 --> 13:41.908
- Hoff offered her a ride,
attacked her in his car.

13:41.951 --> 13:43.561
Nina managed to get away,

13:43.605 --> 13:46.216
but Nina got scared, refused
a rape kit, refused to testify.

13:46.260 --> 13:48.871
- Hoff used a condom.
There was no physical evidence.

13:48.915 --> 13:51.961
So the jury acquitted him.
He started to feel untouchable.

13:52.005 --> 13:53.963
Wanted more,
rape wasn't a good enough high,

13:54.007 --> 13:56.009
so he started killing.

13:56.052 --> 13:59.621
First murder was Denise Bush.

13:59.664 --> 14:02.493
- Hoff allegedly stole
a yellow cab

14:02.537 --> 14:04.408
and started trolling
O'Hare arrivals,

14:04.452 --> 14:05.888
and Denise, just back

14:05.932 --> 14:07.542
from visiting her mom
in Minneapolis,

14:07.585 --> 14:09.109
sadly hailed his cab.

14:09.152 --> 14:10.284
♪

14:10.327 --> 14:12.895
- Next up was Meredith Cheney.

14:12.939 --> 14:15.942
- Meredith got into
a yellow cab late one night

14:15.985 --> 14:17.291
outside of McCormick Place.

14:17.334 --> 14:19.119
Witness described Hoff
as the driver.

14:19.162 --> 14:20.816
Meredith was never seen again.

14:20.860 --> 14:23.210
- No body, no crime.

14:23.253 --> 14:26.604
- Victoria was walking out
of a club on Clark Street

14:26.648 --> 14:28.955
at 2:00 in the morning.
Hoff jumped her.

14:28.998 --> 14:31.609
Witness saw the struggle, but
he was too far away to help.

14:31.653 --> 14:34.308
- But this case,
this Victoria Lee,

14:34.351 --> 14:35.613
that's the one
you nailed him on, right?

14:35.657 --> 14:37.006
- Yeah, we got a lead

14:37.050 --> 14:38.790
on a flop house
he was staying at in Lawndale.

14:38.834 --> 14:41.010
- Martinez suspected
he was bunking here

14:41.054 --> 14:42.925
but had no real proof.

14:42.969 --> 14:44.622
Nothing to get a warrant on.

14:44.666 --> 14:47.669
- So I talked to the roommate,
some dirtbag named Paul Nelson.

14:47.712 --> 14:49.236
I asked him for consent
to search the room.

14:49.279 --> 14:50.585
He told me to suck it.

14:50.628 --> 14:52.587
I politely declined the offer,

14:52.630 --> 14:54.502
then I asked one more time
for consent,

14:54.545 --> 14:56.025
and he spit at me.

14:56.069 --> 14:57.809
So I did what I did.

14:57.853 --> 14:59.550
I beat his ass
with a nightstick,

14:59.594 --> 15:00.987
then told him to sign
the consent form

15:01.030 --> 15:03.206
and unlock Hoff's room.
He agreed.

15:03.250 --> 15:05.774
Went in,
found blood on the shirt.

15:05.817 --> 15:07.907
It was a match
for Victoria's DNA.

15:07.950 --> 15:08.995
Case closed.

15:09.038 --> 15:10.431
- Until the Convictions
Integrity Unit

15:10.474 --> 15:12.085
got a hold of the case files.

15:12.128 --> 15:14.826
- Yeah.
Until then.

15:15.566 --> 15:17.742
Look, Hoff rapes and kills
in quick succession,

15:17.786 --> 15:19.657
so I'm just guessing
he's getting started here.

15:19.701 --> 15:21.094
I were you, I would keep
my eyes and ears open

15:21.137 --> 15:23.487
for any missing persons,
female, affluent,

15:23.531 --> 15:26.360
20s and 30s, North side,
east of Clybourne.

15:26.403 --> 15:28.797
That's where he likes to hunt.

15:30.364 --> 15:31.887
- Appreciate your help, Lisa.

15:34.498 --> 15:36.370
- Any time.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.898
- Stay strong.

15:42.942 --> 15:46.075
Justice and the law don't
always work in perfect harmony.

15:46.119 --> 15:47.947
- Yeah, I've noticed.

15:50.036 --> 15:52.473
I had lunch with Victoria Lee's
father last week.

15:52.516 --> 15:54.518
Poor guy hasn't slept
since Hoff was released.

15:54.562 --> 15:55.911
Sits up at night,

15:55.955 --> 15:57.782
thinking of ways of killing
the son of a bitch.

15:57.826 --> 16:00.002
For real.

16:00.046 --> 16:03.092
I can't even imagine it,
losing your daughter like that,

16:03.136 --> 16:06.400
and having the monster
who did it walk free.

16:18.325 --> 16:19.587
- All right, where are we at?

16:19.630 --> 16:21.371
- Nothing's popping
on missing persons

16:21.415 --> 16:22.720
or reported car thefts.

16:22.764 --> 16:24.026
We got Jay and Hailey
canvassing the area

16:24.070 --> 16:25.549
where the Honda was dumped.
- Huh.

16:25.593 --> 16:27.247
- Hank, I think I got one.

16:27.290 --> 16:28.596
One of my guys on the watch

16:28.639 --> 16:29.945
rolled on
a missing persons call.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.338
- Right.

16:31.381 --> 16:33.557
- Young woman said
her roommate, Renee Ferguson,

16:33.601 --> 16:35.777
got into a ride share
about two hours ago

16:35.820 --> 16:37.692
and never made it
back to the dorms.

16:37.735 --> 16:39.999
Not answering her phone either.
So we ran the phone.

16:40.042 --> 16:42.218
She called 911
about two hours ago.

16:42.262 --> 16:43.741
Listen to this.

16:43.785 --> 16:45.482
- 911, what's your emergency?

16:45.526 --> 16:47.832
- Uh, sir,

16:47.876 --> 16:49.573
this isn't the way.

16:49.617 --> 16:51.967
- Relax, I'm using Waze.
It's a shortcut.

16:52.011 --> 16:54.056
- Dude, this is
the complete wrong direction.

16:54.100 --> 16:55.275
Pull over.

16:55.318 --> 16:56.885
- I'll look into
recently reported stolens.

16:56.928 --> 16:58.582
- [sighs]
Oh, thank you.

16:58.626 --> 17:00.628
I--oh, my God.
No.

17:00.671 --> 17:02.586
Help me.
Help me, please.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.327
Please, do you hear me?
Help me!

17:04.371 --> 17:05.676
Help!
Help!

17:05.720 --> 17:08.114
[crying]
Help!

17:10.116 --> 17:13.075
- The phone cut out before
OEMC could start a trace.

17:13.119 --> 17:15.382
15 seconds later,
the signal was lost.

17:15.425 --> 17:18.559
CPIC's trying to triangulate.
- Tell me you got something.

17:18.602 --> 17:20.039
- [sighs]
13th District,

17:20.082 --> 17:22.476
sitting on a stolen
black Nissan Altima

17:22.519 --> 17:23.868
1/2 block
from Hoff's last dump.

17:23.912 --> 17:25.435
The only problem is,
it's on fire.

17:25.479 --> 17:27.176
- All right, let's go.

17:29.178 --> 17:31.137
- I got a necklace here.

17:34.618 --> 17:36.229
Yeah, it's definitely hers.

17:41.016 --> 17:43.845
- Yo, Sarge, I got footprints
going eastbound.

17:43.888 --> 17:45.673
They good be Hoff's.
He can't be too far.

17:45.716 --> 17:47.718
- Grab Kim.
Chase it.

17:47.762 --> 17:49.720
- Burgess!
Me and you.

17:52.680 --> 17:55.204
Chicago PD!
- Yo, what's going on?

17:55.248 --> 17:56.292
- We're looking for someone.

17:56.336 --> 17:57.511
You see anybody
cut through here?

17:57.554 --> 17:58.642
- Yeah, I saw some jagoff

17:58.686 --> 18:00.035
running by
about 20 minutes ago.

18:00.079 --> 18:01.732
Didn't think too much about it.

18:01.776 --> 18:03.169
Then I saw the smoke
and heard the sirens.

18:03.212 --> 18:04.822
- What'd the jagoff look like?

18:04.866 --> 18:07.042
- I don't know.
A white guy, I guess.

18:07.086 --> 18:09.784
He flagged down a red pickup,
got inside, and took off.

18:11.438 --> 18:12.961
- Sarge, that's a negativeon Hoff,

18:13.004 --> 18:14.528
but we've got a lead
on a red pickup.

18:14.571 --> 18:16.704
- Copy.
Check PODs and cameras.

18:16.747 --> 18:18.358
Keep at it.

18:18.401 --> 18:20.490
- So maybe he pulls up,

18:20.534 --> 18:21.839
grabs Renee from the car,

18:21.883 --> 18:23.189
takes her into
one of those buildings.

18:23.232 --> 18:24.973
- Yeah, he does his thing,
he comes out,

18:25.016 --> 18:26.366
lights the car on fire,
and then he runs.

18:26.409 --> 18:27.715
- All right, round up
some patrol.

18:27.758 --> 18:29.586
We'll start looking.
- Copy that.

18:32.676 --> 18:35.592
[suspenseful music]

18:35.636 --> 18:42.730
♪

18:48.127 --> 18:50.172
- Sergeant!

18:50.216 --> 18:51.739
Found something.

19:21.812 --> 19:22.161
.

19:22.204 --> 19:23.423
[dramatic music]

19:23.466 --> 19:24.728
- Hoff?

19:24.772 --> 19:27.775
- No definitive evidence,
but it's the same MO.

19:28.602 --> 19:31.474
Offender poses as a Quick Route
driver outside a restaurant.

19:31.518 --> 19:33.694
Body worked over
just like the other woman,

19:33.737 --> 19:36.087
naked, tortured, obvious...

19:36.131 --> 19:38.133
horrific signs
of sexual assault.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.569
- Cause of death?

19:39.613 --> 19:41.092
- Blunt force trauma,
head and face.

19:41.136 --> 19:42.746
- Yeah.

19:42.790 --> 19:44.705
So Hoff is on the loose,
doing what he does,

19:44.748 --> 19:47.142
but this time with reckless,
violent abandon.

19:47.186 --> 19:50.014
- Well, it sure seems that way.

19:50.058 --> 19:51.364
- We gotta go public.
- [scoffs]

19:51.407 --> 19:54.193
- We gotta let everyone know
that we believe

19:54.236 --> 19:56.630
Hoff is on a killing spree.

19:56.673 --> 19:57.979
- That's your call.

19:58.022 --> 20:00.199
- We don't have a choice, Hank.
- Sure we do.

20:00.242 --> 20:02.288
You can play this
close to the vest.

20:02.331 --> 20:04.507
We don't have to ID Hoff
by name.

20:05.508 --> 20:07.597
Look, let me
tell you something.

20:07.641 --> 20:09.512
You tell people
what's really going on,

20:09.556 --> 20:10.731
they're gonna come gunning
for you.

20:10.774 --> 20:12.341
They're gonna blame you
for letting him out,

20:12.385 --> 20:14.213
for investigating
the original arrest.

20:14.256 --> 20:16.737
♪

20:16.780 --> 20:18.521
- I can live with that.

20:18.565 --> 20:20.523
I stand by
my original decision.

20:20.567 --> 20:23.265
- Well, it's not me
you gotta convince.

20:23.309 --> 20:25.006
- I'm not trying to,

20:25.049 --> 20:28.052
'cause I'm pretty sure I know
where'd you come out.

20:28.096 --> 20:30.098
- The second
you mention his name,

20:30.141 --> 20:32.187
that guy is gonna take off.

20:32.231 --> 20:34.407
It's gonna make it
a lot harder to find him.

20:36.191 --> 20:38.367
- Just do your job.

20:38.411 --> 20:40.543
You stay one step ahead
of this animal

20:40.587 --> 20:42.284
and bring him in

20:42.328 --> 20:44.199
before he kills again.

20:53.339 --> 20:55.036
Time is of the essence.

20:55.079 --> 20:57.212
- Second victim,
Renee Ferguson,

20:57.256 --> 20:58.822
had skin cells
under her fingernails.

20:58.866 --> 21:01.477
DNA matches to Caleb Hoff.

21:01.521 --> 21:03.262
- All right, thanks.
[phone clacks]

21:03.305 --> 21:04.567
We might be getting closer
to him.

21:04.611 --> 21:06.352
Techs said they found
a receipt in the Nissan

21:06.395 --> 21:07.396
from a Mexican restaurant.

21:07.440 --> 21:09.311
Timestamped at 10:31 a.m.,

21:09.355 --> 21:11.661
which is two hours before
Renee Ferguson's abduction.

21:11.705 --> 21:13.402
- So this guy slams back
a breakfast burrito

21:13.446 --> 21:14.795
and goes on the hunt
for young women.

21:14.838 --> 21:16.013
- Cold-blooded, man.

21:16.057 --> 21:17.363
- All right,
so let's pull video

21:17.406 --> 21:18.451
from that restaurant right now.

21:18.494 --> 21:20.235
Every hour that passes,

21:20.279 --> 21:22.193
another life is in danger.

21:27.111 --> 21:28.852
- Is that him?

21:30.114 --> 21:31.812
- It's not a good shot
of his buddy there.

21:33.379 --> 21:35.555
Facial rec will have
a hard time getting a read.

21:35.598 --> 21:37.774
- I can't believe
we let a monster like Hoff

21:37.818 --> 21:39.776
just walk out of prison.

21:39.820 --> 21:42.605
- Oh, come on, Hailey.
Didn't have a choice.

21:42.649 --> 21:43.998
- Sure we did.

21:44.041 --> 21:45.129
We just picked the one that

21:45.173 --> 21:46.217
made all the powerful people
in this city

21:46.261 --> 21:48.655
feel warm and fuzzy.

21:48.698 --> 21:50.787
- You don't really
believe that, do you?

21:50.831 --> 21:52.659
- I do.

21:52.702 --> 21:55.575
- So are you saying
you condone police misconduct?

21:56.663 --> 21:58.055
- Of course not.

21:58.099 --> 21:59.666
I'm saying, if it happens,

21:59.709 --> 22:01.798
if somebody acts
inappropriately,

22:01.842 --> 22:02.973
it doesn't mean we need

22:03.017 --> 22:05.367
to light the whole damn villageon fire.

22:05.411 --> 22:07.195
- I'm not really sure I know

22:07.238 --> 22:09.806
what it is
you're trying to say here.

22:09.850 --> 22:12.113
- What I'm trying to say

22:12.156 --> 22:15.072
is those two women
would still be alive

22:15.116 --> 22:18.032
if the prosecutor who looked
into Hoff's initial arrest

22:18.075 --> 22:19.947
had just looked the other way.

22:22.384 --> 22:24.343
- And here we are.

22:25.648 --> 22:26.867
[knocks]

22:31.219 --> 22:33.090
- Sorry to bother you.
I called a few times.

22:33.134 --> 22:34.744
Never heard back, so...
- Sorry.

22:34.788 --> 22:37.268
I don't check my phone too much
these days.

22:37.878 --> 22:40.359
- Listen, I got a few more
questions about Hoff.

22:40.402 --> 22:43.057
I just was hoping
I could pick your brain.

22:43.100 --> 22:45.407
- Sure, come on in.
- Thanks.

22:48.497 --> 22:50.456
- World's upside down, Hank.

22:50.499 --> 22:52.371
Where you guys at?

22:52.414 --> 22:54.068
- We found his DNA
under the fingernails

22:54.111 --> 22:56.375
of one of the victims,

22:56.418 --> 22:58.899
so we now have proof it's him.

22:58.942 --> 23:00.161
- Let me guess:

23:00.204 --> 23:02.468
Renee's, right?

23:02.511 --> 23:04.905
She looks like a fighter.

23:04.948 --> 23:06.602
We weren't so lucky.

23:06.646 --> 23:08.648
Hoff kept covering his tracks
at every turn,

23:08.691 --> 23:12.391
which is why I ultimately
did what I did.

23:12.434 --> 23:13.957
I was afraid
we'd never catch him,

23:14.001 --> 23:15.481
that he'd keep on killing.

23:16.917 --> 23:19.963
If I had just waited,
stayed patient,

23:20.007 --> 23:21.922
played by the rules,
he'd still be in jail,

23:21.965 --> 23:24.141
and those two girls
would still be alive.

23:24.185 --> 23:26.796
- Listen, listen to me.

23:26.840 --> 23:29.451
You did what you had to do
in that moment

23:29.495 --> 23:32.280
to make this city safer,

23:32.323 --> 23:34.630
make sure he didn't kill
more innocent women.

23:36.676 --> 23:38.765
You got nothing
to apologize for.

23:41.855 --> 23:43.770
- [sighs]

23:43.813 --> 23:46.381
- Look, we found
a photo of Hoff

23:46.425 --> 23:48.818
with an unknown male, white.

23:50.733 --> 23:53.301
I thought you might know
who he is.

23:53.344 --> 23:55.738
- Kenny Rose, meth dealer.
- Huh.

23:55.782 --> 23:58.393
- He and Hoff grew up
in the same foster home.

23:59.438 --> 24:00.917
- Well, Kenny has
an impressive sheet.

24:00.961 --> 24:03.659
Meth, coke, heroin,
and two armed robbery charges,

24:03.703 --> 24:05.400
you know, for good measure.

24:05.444 --> 24:07.837
And he drives
a 2014 red Ford pickup.

24:07.881 --> 24:09.360
It matches
what our witness told us.

24:09.404 --> 24:13.364
- All right, so Hoff ditches
the stolen Nissan, torches it,

24:13.408 --> 24:15.105
his buddy Rose pulls up
in the pickup,

24:15.149 --> 24:16.237
helps Hoff get away.

24:16.280 --> 24:17.499
- It means Rose knew
what Hoff was doing.

24:17.543 --> 24:19.327
- And he's helping him
get away with it.

24:19.370 --> 24:20.459
All right,
I'll loop in the team.

24:20.502 --> 24:22.461
Let Voight know.
- Yeah.

24:22.504 --> 24:25.812
[dramatic music]

24:26.334 --> 24:27.770
- We got a red truck
coming this way.

24:27.814 --> 24:30.773
- Mm-hmm.

24:30.817 --> 24:32.601
Yep.
The plate's a match.

24:32.645 --> 24:34.864
One driver.
That's probably Rose.

24:34.908 --> 24:36.170
No sign of Hoff.

24:36.213 --> 24:38.085
- All right, let him park.

24:38.128 --> 24:40.740
We'll take him before
he goes inside the house.

24:40.783 --> 24:42.524
- Copy that.

24:42.568 --> 24:45.396
[suspenseful music]

24:45.440 --> 24:52.491
♪

25:05.025 --> 25:07.244
- Chicago PD!

25:07.288 --> 25:08.898
Don't run!

25:21.868 --> 25:23.957
- Rose is running out the back.
We're clearing the house.

25:24.000 --> 25:26.437
- Copy that.

25:26.481 --> 25:28.439
- Chicago PD!

25:34.315 --> 25:35.316
- Don't move, you hear me?

25:35.359 --> 25:36.665
Put your hands
behind your back.

25:43.237 --> 25:44.412
- We got him.

25:44.455 --> 25:46.109
- Don't fight.
What do you got on you, huh?

25:46.153 --> 25:47.850
Huh?

25:47.894 --> 25:49.809
What's that?
That's crystal meth, Kenny.

25:49.852 --> 25:51.288
Your day just got
a lot worse.

25:51.332 --> 25:52.768
Get up.

25:54.117 --> 25:55.466
- Where's Caleb Hoff?

25:55.510 --> 25:57.164
- Who?

25:57.207 --> 25:58.992
- Your friend who likes
to rape and kill women.

25:59.035 --> 26:00.036
- I don't got any friends
like that.

26:00.080 --> 26:01.690
You guys must have
the wrong house.

26:01.734 --> 26:03.997
- We can do this the easy way,
or we can do it the other way.

26:04.040 --> 26:05.433
Kenny, it's up to you.

26:07.130 --> 26:08.871
- I choose option two,
the other way.

26:08.915 --> 26:11.134
- You sure about that?
- I'm positive.

26:11.178 --> 26:16.531
♪

26:16.575 --> 26:18.011
- Bring him inside.

26:18.054 --> 26:23.494
♪

26:23.538 --> 26:25.148
- Take him.

26:25.192 --> 26:32.112
♪

26:38.509 --> 26:38.684
.

26:38.727 --> 26:40.424
- All right, Sarge,
the house is clear,

26:40.468 --> 26:41.687
and I found this jacket.

26:41.730 --> 26:42.731
Hoff was wearing it
during the first murder,

26:42.775 --> 26:43.993
and this is what he was wearing

26:44.037 --> 26:45.212
outside the mini-market
in that video.

26:45.255 --> 26:46.430
So he was definitely
hanging out around here.

26:46.474 --> 26:49.695
- We also found more meth.
Two ounces or so.

26:49.738 --> 26:51.305
- It's enough to arrest him,

26:51.348 --> 26:53.176
but it might not be enough to
leverage him into cooperating.

26:53.220 --> 26:54.961
- Yeah, well,
let me worry about that.

26:55.004 --> 26:56.353
- What does that mean?

26:56.397 --> 26:58.007
- It doesn't matter
what it means, Jay.

26:58.051 --> 26:59.792
- I know you're upset.
- Upset?

27:00.444 --> 27:03.012
That's funny, I'm not sure
I know what that means.

27:03.056 --> 27:04.535
- Sarge, we all want
to nail this guy.

27:04.579 --> 27:06.189
- Why don't you guys
head back to the district,

27:06.233 --> 27:08.452
see if you can locate
Hoff's whereabouts?

27:09.410 --> 27:10.933
Adam and I,

27:10.977 --> 27:12.674
we're gonna talk to Rose
one more time,

27:12.718 --> 27:14.981
see if we can convince him
to cooperate.

27:17.244 --> 27:20.073
- Sarge.
- This is not a negotiation.

27:22.815 --> 27:24.468
So go!

27:26.688 --> 27:27.646
- Come on, you guys.

27:29.256 --> 27:31.258
Hoff's still out there.
We got work to do.

27:43.487 --> 27:46.577
- You good?
- You know I'm good.

27:47.491 --> 27:50.277
- Let's do it.

27:54.934 --> 27:56.544
- [sighs]

27:56.587 --> 27:59.068
- Okay, that's a felony
right there.

27:59.112 --> 28:01.941
- Certainly enough to violate
your parole.

28:01.984 --> 28:03.551
- Do what you gotta do.

28:04.987 --> 28:07.990
- We can pretend
we never found this meth,

28:08.034 --> 28:11.559
came over,
asked you a few questions.

28:11.602 --> 28:13.213
You helped us out.

28:13.256 --> 28:15.345
- I don't know nothing
about Hoff.

28:15.389 --> 28:18.958
- He raped and murdered two
women in the last 48 hours...

28:21.221 --> 28:24.703
Violated them in ways

28:24.746 --> 28:26.966
I won't even describe.

28:29.533 --> 28:30.883
- I want a lawyer.

28:30.926 --> 28:32.754
- You want a lawyer, huh?

28:32.798 --> 28:34.495
Kenny...

28:36.192 --> 28:38.717
You don't cooperate...

28:41.458 --> 28:43.722
You're gonna need a priest.

28:43.765 --> 28:46.333
- What the hell are you--
- Where's Caleb Hoff?

28:46.376 --> 28:48.378
- Tell us where he is, Kenny.
- Where is he?

28:48.422 --> 28:49.815
- Tell us where he is.
It's gonna be a lot easier.

28:49.858 --> 28:50.946
Trust me.
- Where is he?

28:50.990 --> 28:52.513
- I said I want a lawyer.

29:04.786 --> 29:07.702
- [heavy breathing]

29:09.312 --> 29:11.401
Pinch him
on the meth possession.

29:23.587 --> 29:27.113
[car door clicks shut]
[car engines starting]

29:49.004 --> 29:52.094
[grunting]

29:52.138 --> 29:54.836
- Hey, what the hell
are you doing?

29:55.576 --> 29:58.187
Hey, you can't mess up
the guy's car like that.

29:58.231 --> 30:00.842
Are you crazy or something?

30:00.886 --> 30:02.626
I'm about to call the cops!

30:02.670 --> 30:04.063
- There's no need.

30:04.106 --> 30:06.239
Cops are already on the scene.

30:06.282 --> 30:08.197
- What--what does that
even mean?

30:08.241 --> 30:10.547
- It means it's time for you
to walk away now.

30:11.897 --> 30:14.464
You understand me?

30:14.508 --> 30:15.770
Now!

30:22.385 --> 30:24.257
- Guys, I got
CTA security footage

30:24.300 --> 30:26.650
of Hoff getting on the L
two blocks from Rose's house.

30:26.694 --> 30:28.043
- What time?

30:28.087 --> 30:29.828
- 4:22 p.m. today.

30:29.871 --> 30:31.177
- There's only two trains
that make that stop.

30:31.220 --> 30:32.439
- Pink and purple.

30:32.482 --> 30:33.701
- If he got on the L,
he had to get off.

30:33.744 --> 30:35.224
We should check surveillance
at all stops,

30:35.268 --> 30:36.835
scanning in both directions.

30:39.098 --> 30:42.014
[quiet foreboding music]

30:42.057 --> 30:49.195
♪

30:57.943 --> 31:00.859
[cell phone buzzing]

31:09.215 --> 31:10.390
- Voight.

31:10.433 --> 31:12.479
- Sarge, Hoff exited the L

31:12.522 --> 31:15.047
at Kostner Street Station
today at 5:02 p.m.

31:15.090 --> 31:16.570
- Kostner.

31:16.613 --> 31:18.441
Do we know any reason
he'd be there?

31:18.485 --> 31:21.444
Any family, any known
associates in the area?

31:21.488 --> 31:23.098
- Not sure.
I reached out to Martinez.

31:23.142 --> 31:24.186
She drew a blank.

31:24.230 --> 31:25.144
- Wait a minute.
Hold on a second.

31:25.187 --> 31:26.667
Hold on.

31:26.710 --> 31:29.670
All right, I want you to run
a name for me.

31:30.671 --> 31:33.065
Victor.
Victor Silvano.

31:33.108 --> 31:34.196
Run the name Victor Silvano.

31:34.240 --> 31:36.198
- Okay, I'm on it.

31:36.242 --> 31:38.766
[keys clacking]
Victor Silvano...

31:40.202 --> 31:42.204
Died nine months ago,
no wife and kids,

31:42.248 --> 31:44.380
LKA is somewhere
on the South side.

31:44.424 --> 31:46.034
He worked as
an assistant foreman

31:46.078 --> 31:47.470
for 23 years
at Galloway Metals.

31:47.514 --> 31:48.819
- Hold on.
That's three blocks

31:48.863 --> 31:50.082
north of Kostner.

31:50.125 --> 31:51.518
It went out of business
two years ago.

31:51.561 --> 31:52.736
- A good place to hide.

31:53.955 --> 31:55.217
- Gear up.

31:55.261 --> 31:56.915
I'm ten minutes out.

32:01.963 --> 32:02.181
.

32:02.224 --> 32:04.792
[dramatic music]

32:04.835 --> 32:11.364
♪

32:12.539 --> 32:14.454
- Jay, it's me.
I'm here on site.

32:14.497 --> 32:16.282
I'm dropping anchor.

32:16.325 --> 32:17.587
I'll wait for your arrival.

32:17.631 --> 32:19.328
- On our way, Sarge.

32:19.372 --> 32:21.200
- Okay.
Copy that.

32:21.243 --> 32:24.203
[uneasy music]

32:24.246 --> 32:31.166
♪

32:38.652 --> 32:40.349
[rattling]

32:54.146 --> 32:56.713
Lisa, what the hell
are you doing here?

32:56.757 --> 32:58.106
- Go home.
Let me take it from here.

32:58.150 --> 33:00.239
[gunshots]

33:00.282 --> 33:03.024
- 5021, shots fired
at the police.

33:03.068 --> 33:07.028
On site, Galloway Metals,
2133 Rexford Road.

33:07.072 --> 33:08.769
- Copy that.
- Lisa.

33:08.812 --> 33:10.597
- Backup en route.

33:10.640 --> 33:14.166
♪

33:14.209 --> 33:17.299
- Jay, be advised.
I'm heading inside the factory.

33:17.343 --> 33:18.779
- Copy that.
We're almost there.

33:18.822 --> 33:21.738
[suspenseful music]

33:21.782 --> 33:28.876
♪

33:35.839 --> 33:37.711
[gunshots]

33:39.582 --> 33:41.889
[gunshots]
Come out, Hoff!

33:44.544 --> 33:47.982
[gunshots]

33:52.160 --> 33:55.294
[gunshots]

33:56.121 --> 33:57.339
- Agh!

33:57.383 --> 34:00.299
[gun clicks]
Damn it!

34:00.342 --> 34:03.041
[gunshots]

34:04.085 --> 34:06.522
- Okay.
- You're empty, Caleb.

34:06.566 --> 34:09.003
- Okay!
Don't shoot.

34:10.744 --> 34:13.007
- Put the gun down.

34:13.051 --> 34:15.009
Now!

34:17.316 --> 34:18.926
Give me a reason.

34:31.243 --> 34:32.200
[scoffs]

34:32.244 --> 34:35.203
- [moaning]

34:35.247 --> 34:38.163
[heavy breathing]

34:40.078 --> 34:43.472
- Hey.
Go ahead.

34:43.516 --> 34:45.909
Do it.
Come on.

34:47.085 --> 34:49.478
Come on, tough guy.
Reach for the gun.

34:50.479 --> 34:52.481
Do it.

34:52.525 --> 34:53.874
Do it!

35:00.968 --> 35:02.578
- Get away from him.

35:02.622 --> 35:03.971
- Martinez.

35:04.014 --> 35:05.755
- Let me do this, Hank.

35:05.799 --> 35:07.409
Let me make this right.

35:07.453 --> 35:08.628
- Hey, Lisa, look at me.

35:08.671 --> 35:10.978
- I've been dreaming about this
for a while.

35:11.021 --> 35:14.721
Watching you crawl,
beg for your worthless life.

35:14.764 --> 35:15.896
- Look at me.
It's not worth it.

35:15.939 --> 35:17.115
- Making you feel the pain
you inflicted

35:17.158 --> 35:18.638
on those innocent women.
- Look at me.

35:18.681 --> 35:19.595
- Watching you bleed out,
gasp--

35:19.639 --> 35:21.119
[gunshot]

35:22.250 --> 35:23.817
- Sarge, we're here!
Are you hit?

35:23.860 --> 35:25.949
- I'm good!
I got Hoff right here!

35:25.993 --> 35:28.604
Go home.
Get the hell out of here now.

35:28.648 --> 35:29.997
It's not worth it.
Go.

35:31.477 --> 35:33.131
Go!

35:38.005 --> 35:39.963
Caleb Hoff, hey.

35:40.007 --> 35:42.096
- [screams][moans]

35:42.140 --> 35:43.967
- You're under arrest

35:44.011 --> 35:46.883
for the murders of Jess Larson

35:46.927 --> 35:49.495
and Renee Ferguson.

35:49.538 --> 35:54.804
- [grunting]

35:54.848 --> 35:56.589
- Everything all right?

35:58.156 --> 35:59.374
- I think Caleb here

35:59.418 --> 36:01.246
hurt himself jumping
off that walkway, though.

36:01.289 --> 36:03.509
- Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

36:04.336 --> 36:06.990
- Is there anything I need
to know or not know?

36:07.034 --> 36:09.079
- We're good.

36:09.123 --> 36:12.126
Guess the guy thought
he could fly or something.

36:16.522 --> 36:19.177
Yeah, we chased a hunch
he was hiding off of Kostner.

36:19.220 --> 36:21.396
He had an uncle that used
to work at Galloway Metals.

36:22.571 --> 36:25.008
I checked it out,
and he was there.

36:25.052 --> 36:26.619
- Great work.
- Thank you.

36:26.662 --> 36:29.535
- According to the report,
he had a fractured right tibia.

36:29.578 --> 36:31.972
- Yeah, he tried to escape,

36:32.015 --> 36:33.234
jumped off the second floor,

36:33.278 --> 36:35.541
so I guess that makes sense.

36:37.282 --> 36:40.023
- I'm just pleasantly surprised
that his face is clean.

36:40.067 --> 36:42.330
No bruises, no cuts.

36:43.853 --> 36:45.333
- Like I said,

36:45.377 --> 36:47.857
jumped off the second floor,
fell awkwardly.

36:48.510 --> 36:50.817
Handcuffed him,
got him medical attention,

36:50.860 --> 36:52.514
brought him back
to the district.

36:52.558 --> 36:54.647
- I was trying to pay you
a compliment, Sergeant.

36:54.690 --> 36:56.039
A guy like this,

36:56.083 --> 36:58.303
I'm guessing it's easy
to find a reason

36:58.346 --> 37:00.479
to subdue him.

37:00.522 --> 37:02.132
- I just wanted
to make the arrest,

37:02.176 --> 37:05.179
get this guy back in a cage
where he belongs.

37:05.223 --> 37:08.574
No point giving his lawyer
another loophole.

37:08.617 --> 37:10.053
- I agree.
The problem is

37:10.097 --> 37:11.490
that they've already found one,

37:11.533 --> 37:14.232
or they're claiming
to have found one.

37:15.233 --> 37:16.930
- What are you talking about?

37:16.973 --> 37:19.237
- Hoff claims
that Detective Martinez

37:19.280 --> 37:21.064
was at the scene of the arrest.

37:23.066 --> 37:24.546
Is there any truth to that?

37:27.157 --> 37:30.117
- I arrived on scene,
solo, around 7:21.

37:31.640 --> 37:33.338
Waited for backup.

37:33.381 --> 37:36.079
We located Hoff inside
the abandoned factory,

37:36.123 --> 37:37.342
jumped off the second fl--

37:37.385 --> 37:40.301
- Right, and he fell awkwardly.

37:40.345 --> 37:42.434
You placed him under arrest,
got him medical attention,

37:42.477 --> 37:44.653
and brought him down
to the district.

37:44.697 --> 37:46.960
Was Martinez there?

37:49.092 --> 37:51.225
Just tell me the truth, Hank.

37:53.271 --> 37:55.185
- The truth is not your friend
right now, Sam.

37:55.229 --> 37:58.232
So if I were you,

37:58.276 --> 38:00.800
I'd stop asking questions.

38:01.670 --> 38:04.369
I mean, what matters,
what really matters...

38:05.848 --> 38:07.676
Is a violent, evil man

38:07.720 --> 38:09.591
is now in custody,

38:09.635 --> 38:12.420
and the evidence against him
is overwhelming.

38:14.292 --> 38:17.643
So, I mean, please,

38:17.686 --> 38:20.167
just take yes for an answer
and move on.

38:28.393 --> 38:31.004
- I appreciate you stopping by,

38:31.047 --> 38:32.875
but you don't have to worry
about me.

38:32.919 --> 38:35.487
I'm not gonna do
anything crazy.

38:35.530 --> 38:38.968
- Hmm.
- Not tonight, at least.

38:39.012 --> 38:41.580
- Day by day,
that's all we can do.

38:46.498 --> 38:49.239
- I dedicated my whole
damn life to this city,

38:49.283 --> 38:51.241
to being a cop,

38:51.285 --> 38:53.331
woke up every day
trying to do good,

38:53.374 --> 38:55.376
trying to make Chicago

38:55.420 --> 38:57.726
a better place to live,

38:57.770 --> 39:00.250
a safer place to live.

39:00.294 --> 39:02.601
I did a lot of good things.

39:02.644 --> 39:04.385
I made a difference.

39:04.429 --> 39:07.823
Took hundreds of really violent
men, rapists and killers,

39:07.867 --> 39:09.434
off the street.

39:09.477 --> 39:12.915
I didn't ask
for medals or trophies.

39:12.959 --> 39:15.570
I just did my job,
put in my hours,

39:15.614 --> 39:17.006
'cause I enjoyed it.

39:17.050 --> 39:19.357
'Cause it made me feel good.

39:21.881 --> 39:23.709
That's all over.

39:23.752 --> 39:25.928
They took that away from me.

39:25.972 --> 39:27.974
Now I'm just a punchline,

39:28.017 --> 39:30.716
a cowboy cop
who lost her damn mind.

39:33.283 --> 39:36.678
The thing that really hurts is,

39:36.722 --> 39:40.116
the politicians and the press
picked Hoff over me.

39:41.596 --> 39:44.556
They turned him into a monster
and made him a saint.

39:46.471 --> 39:47.733
- [sighs]

39:49.561 --> 39:52.390
They just don't think
the way we do, you know?

39:53.565 --> 39:56.350
They're always worried
about the way things look,

39:56.394 --> 39:58.831
what people might say.

39:58.874 --> 40:01.094
For us,

40:01.137 --> 40:03.401
for real cops, it's simple.

40:04.793 --> 40:06.926
I mean, you did the only thing
you could do

40:06.969 --> 40:09.102
in that moment
to make things better.

40:10.582 --> 40:11.757
Safer.

40:15.064 --> 40:16.588
[sighs]

40:24.465 --> 40:26.424
I think this belongs to you.

40:31.341 --> 40:33.126
- We think alike.

40:35.781 --> 40:37.347
- I think we do.

40:40.307 --> 40:42.614
Thanks for the drink.

40:59.674 --> 40:59.892
.

40:59.935 --> 41:02.851
[dramatic music]

41:02.895 --> 41:09.815
♪
